Unit Testing Plan

The purpose of unit testing is to test the components of the system to ensure they function correctly.

Test Case 1: Add Patient
  Input: Valid patient information
  Expected Result: Patient is added to the system

Test Case 2: View Patients
  Input: Existing patient list
  Expected Result: All patients are displayed correctly

Test Case 3: Schedule Appointment
  Input: Valid patient and appointment details
  Expected Result: Appointment is successfully scheduled

Test Case 4: Input Validation
  Input: Missing required fields
  Expected Result: System displays an error message
